name: DataRenderer
text: An abstract base class for data renderer types (e.g. GlyphRenderer, TileRenderer).

attrs.name: image_source
descs: Image source to use when rendering on the plot.

attrs.name: render_parents
descs: Flag enable/disable drawing of parent tiles while waiting for new tiles to arrive. Default value is True.

name: GlyphRenderer

attrs.name: data_source
descs: Local data source to use when rendering glyphs on the plot.

attrs.name: glyph
descs:
The glyph to render, in conjunction with the supplied data source
and ranges.

attrs.name: hover_glyph
descs:
An optional glyph used for inspected points, e.g., those that are
being hovered over by a HoverTool.

attrs.name: nonselection_glyph
descs:
An optional glyph used for explicitly non-selected points
(i.e., non-selected when there are other points that are selected,
but not when no points at all are selected.)

attrs.name: selection_glyph
descs: An optional glyph used for selected points.

attrs.name: x_range_name
descs:
A particular (named) x-range to use for computing screen
locations when rendering glyphs on the plot. If unset, use the
default x-range.

attrs.name: y_range_name
descs:
A particular (named) y-range to use for computing screen
locations when rendering glyphs on the plot. If unset, use the
default -range.

name: GuideRenderer
text:
A base class for all guide renderer types. GuideRenderer is
not generally useful to instantiate on its own.

attrs.name: plot
descs: The plot to which this guide renderer is attached.

name: Renderer
text: An abstract base class for renderer types.

attrs.name: level
descs: Specifies the level in which to paint this renderer.

attrs.name: visible
descs: Is the renderer visible. Default: True

attrs.name: render_parents
descs: Flag enable/disable drawing of parent tiles while waiting for new tiles to arrive. Default value is True.

attrs.name: tile_source
descs: Local data source to use when rendering glyphs on the plot.

attrs.name: x_range_name
descs:
A particular (named) x-range to use for computing screen
locations when rendering glyphs on the plot. If unset, use the
default x-range.

attrs.name: y_range_name
descs:
A particular (named) y-range to use for computing screen
locations when rendering glyphs on the plot. If unset, use the
default y-range.
